C. E. Hultquist, appellant, v. Lena Humphreys, appellee.Gen. No. 25,978.Action for commissions as a real estate broker. Judgment for defendant on a directed verdict. Appeal from the Municipal Court of Chicago; the Hon. William N. Gemmill, Judge, presiding. Heard in the Branch Appellate Court at the March term, 1920.Affirmed.

Taylor, J., dissenting.

Opinion filed November 2, 1921.Monahan & Monahan, for appellant. Charles M. Haft, for appellee. Mr. Presiding Justice O’Connor

delivered the opinion of the court.
